Meet <b>Crystal</b> our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Crystal has been relaxing at her plush <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=queen6494311"><a href='/home/?user=queen6494311'>1021-G Cherry Blossom Road</a> </a> hideaway in Ravenwood for quite some time now. She moved to Millsberry way back on December 17th, 2007. It looks like Crystal is coming up on her one-year anniversary in Millsberry. <br><br>Crystal has been busy since moving to Millsberry and she has the trophies to prove it. She has some gold for Hop and Drop, Sink Three, Rope Climb, Home Run Derby, and Sudoku.<br><br>Crystal loves Ravenwood and all of the historic architecture in the neighborhood. It's nice for the occasional stroll and Crystal loves to explore the <a href="http://millsberry.com/main_map.phtml?location=ravenwood">neighborhood</a>. <br><br>Crystal describes herself as shy, knowledgeable, and friendly. She might be able to help you with your homework, but you'll probably have to ask her for help sense she's a little timid.  <br><br>Her interests include drawing, drawing, and more drawing. After all, they say good things come in threes. <br><br>If you're looking for Crystal your best bet is to check the amusement park, the playground or maybe the tree mall. <br><br>Next time you bump into Crystal, make sure you give her a big Millsberry smile and thank her for being such an outstanding citizen!<br></div>
